11 An Act relating to higher education; amending 70 O.S.
2021, Section 4663, as amended by Section 1, Chapter
12 230, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 4663),
which relates to the board of trustees for Oklahoma
13 State University/Tulsa; striking Board of Trustees
authorization to promulgate rules and enact policies
14 to govern the processes and procedures of the Board;
deleting obsolete transition language; striking
15 process for selection of the president of Oklahoma
State University/Tulsa; and providing an effective
16 date.
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 4663, as
21 amended by Section 1, Chapter 230, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025,
22 Section 4663), is amended to read as follows:
23 Section 4663. A. On January 1, 1999, there shall be created
24 the Board of Trustees for Oklahoma State University/Tulsa which
HB4363 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 shal l consist of seven members who reside in Tulsa County or
2 contiguous counties, one member of the Board of Regents for the
3 Oklahoma Agricultural and Mechanical Colleges (A&M Board) who shall
4 reside in the First Congressional District, and one member who shall
5 be appointed by the chair of the A&M Board. The member of the A&M
6 Board and the member appointed by the chair of the A&M Board shall
7 serve as voting, ex officio members. For purposes of serving on the
8 Board of Trustees, the member of the A&M Board and the member
9 appointed by the chair of the A&M Board who are appointed to the
10 Board of Trustees shall not be subject to the dual office holding
11 restrictions in Section 6 of Title 51 of the Oklahoma Statutes. The
12 Governor shall appoint the other members of the Board of Trustees
13 with the advice and consent of the Senate. The members shall be
14 appointed to numbered positions with staggered terms to expire as
15 provided in this section. Successors to the initial board members
16 shall serve seven-year terms that shall expire on June 30 of the
17 seventh year following appointment. Vacancies on the Board shall be
18 filled for the unexpired term by the Governor with the advice and
19 consent of the Senate. The member of the A&M Board who resides in
20 the First Congressional District shall hold position number eight.
21 The member appointed by the chair of the A&M Board shall hold
22 position number nine. The numbered positions and terms shall be as
23 follows:
24
