BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 9. Position No. 9: The term of office shall be at the
2 direction of the chair of the A&M Board.
3 B. The Board of Trustees shall be a body corporate and shall
4 adopt and use an official seal. The Board shall elect a chair, vice
5 chair, and secretary annually, each of whom shall serve for a term
6 of one fiscal year and until a successor is elected and qualified,
7 and who shall perform such duties as the Board directs. The Board
8 shall adopt rules which it deems necessary for the operation of the
9 Board and the discharge of its duties and shall cause the minutes of
10 all meetings to be kept. The Board shall comply with the Oklahoma
11 Open Meeting Act and the Oklahoma Open Records Act.
12 C. The Board of Trustees for Oklahoma State University/Tulsa
13 may be authorized by the A&M Board to supervise and manage the
14 campus of Oklahoma State University/Tulsa and perform other
15 functions as necessary. The Board of Trustees shall promulgate
16 rules and enact policies to govern the processes and procedures of
17 the Board. It is the intent of the Legislature that in the
18 interests of immediate responsiveness to the needs of students,
19 employees, and the business community that the decision or approval
20 process be expedited.
21 D. On or after January 1, 1999, the A&M Board may assign and
22 delineate roles and responsibilities for the Board of Trustees for
23 Oklahoma State University/Tulsa. Such responsibilities may include,
24 but are not limited to, student services, facility operations,
HB4363 HFLR Page 4
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 stud ent financial services, budget preparations, endowed chairs at
2 Oklahoma State University/Tulsa, and administrative operations as
3 specified by the A&M Board.
4 E. The Board of Trustees shall establish the usual and
5 customary accounts established by higher education institutions
6 within the Office of Management and Enterprise Services necessary to
7 carry out its duties.
8 F. Until July 1, 2001, during the transition and development of
9 Oklahoma State University/Tulsa, acting on behalf of the Board of
10 Trustees for Oklahoma State University/Tulsa, Oklahoma State
11 University is authorized and directed to negotiate contracts with
12 institutions for courses and degree programs of study approved by
13 the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education, as necessary to
14 meet the higher education needs for the Tulsa metropolitan area.
15 The number of degree programs offered by Northeastern State
16 University and Langston University shall not be diminished or
17 duplicated.
18 G. The president of Oklahoma State University/Tulsa shall be
19 selected by the Board of Regents for the Oklahoma Agricultural and
20 Mechanical Colleges after completion of a search process as set
21 forth in this subsection. The A&M Board shall appoint at least two
22 of its members, one of whom must reside in the First Congressional
23 District, and the Board of Trustees shall appoint at least two of
24 its members to a search committee. The president of Oklahoma State
HB4363 HFLR Page 5
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Univ ersity may appoint other representatives of faculty, staff, and
2 students to the search committee. The president of Oklahoma State
3 University shall recommend a candidate in consultation with the
4 search committee to the Board of Trustees and the A&M Board.
5 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
6
